race.description: Jacquinot First Yearlings @ Widden Mdn Plate
race.comment: MISS SUPERNOVA (14) disappointed on debut then had a six-week let-up and improved out of sight last start, charging home late to miss by a whisker over this distance at Randwick. Maps beautifully and will be tough to hold out. MANUKAU (6) started at a short quote but found one better when returning from a 37-week break over 1300m at Hawkesbury last time out. Will race handy from a good gate and with the run under the belt is going to be right in the finish. The interesting runner is VERLANDER (2) whose only appearance to date was in Switzerland's Todman Stakes in March 2024. Now a gelding and looked sharp winning a Rosehill trial recently. Could easily blow them away. LIPSTICK (12) returns from an eight-month spell and is a new arrival in the Waller stable. Showed enough in three runs to date to suggest she will be competitive. Stablemate NANDINA (15) is a debutante by So You Think from top race mare Catkins. Has trialled six times so she should know what it is all about.
